Authorities at Aitape in the West Sepik province, on Papua New Guinea's northwest coast, said the tsunami that hit the coast west of the village on Friday night had wiped out three villages and had almost completely destroyed another.
The Papua New Guinea Defense Force was on standby Sunday and police and health services officials expected the official death toll of 71 to rise.
Foreign Affairs Minister Alexander Downer said a Royal Australian Air Force C-130 Hercules aircraft now in Papua New Guinea on training exercises would be diverted to deliver relief supplies.
